511
00:25:21,330 --> 00:25:22,206
- Okay!

512
00:25:22,206 --> 00:25:27,206
(men chattering)
(Jimmer shouting)

513
00:25:30,923 --> 00:25:32,373
- [Albert] Get your butt up there!

514
00:25:32,373 --> 00:25:35,206
(Jimmer shouting)

515
00:25:36,939 --> 00:25:40,989
Another was, all of a sudden,
he could drink like a fish.

516
00:25:42,540 --> 00:25:43,539
- [Reuben] Hang on,
Jimmer, hang on, hang on.

517
00:25:49,831 --> 00:25:50,704
- Look what I got, eh?

518
00:25:50,704 --> 00:25:51,885
- Oh!

519
00:25:51,885 --> 00:25:53,704
- Don't that look nice?

520
00:25:53,704 --> 00:25:55,311
- [Jimmer] Boodebeeboop!

521
00:25:55,311 --> 00:25:57,228
- It's okay, it's okay.

522
00:25:59,583 --> 00:26:00,416
There ya go.

523
00:26:00,416 --> 00:26:03,502
- [Albert] The Jimmer had
become a living legend,

524
00:26:03,502 --> 00:26:04,576
and not because he'd been abducted.

525
00:26:04,576 --> 00:26:06,861
We get two or three of those a year.

526
00:26:06,861 --> 00:26:08,776
- Two, three!

527
00:26:08,776 --> 00:26:11,346
- [Albert] It was his
capacity for drinking

528
00:26:11,346 --> 00:26:14,046
that spread through all the
watering holes in the U.P.

529
00:26:16,391 --> 00:26:19,280
(Jimmer screams)

530
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:20,964
- With a whisky chaser!

531
00:26:20,964 --> 00:26:23,830
- With a whisky chaser!

532
00:26:23,830 --> 00:26:25,747
- With a whisky chaser!

533
00:26:27,396 --> 00:26:29,256
- [Albert] The regulars
up to the Porcelain Bus

534
00:26:29,256 --> 00:26:31,476
compare him to the late, great Himel Hyman

535
00:26:31,476 --> 00:26:33,416
in the Cup-o-harder,
known amongst the Injuns

536
00:26:33,416 --> 00:26:36,059
as the Great White Stomach.

537
00:26:37,373 --> 00:26:39,096
Himel made a nice living drinking

538
00:26:39,096 --> 00:26:41,266
any and all things put in front of him,

539
00:26:41,266 --> 00:26:44,326
including that fateful
bucket of week-old wastewater

540
00:26:44,326 --> 00:26:47,536
from the bilge of a
Scandinavian oil barge,

541
00:26:47,536 --> 00:26:48,716
God rest his soul.

542
00:26:48,716 --> 00:26:50,626
Jimmer Negamanee from Menominee

543
00:26:50,626 --> 00:26:52,889
was cut from the same piece of cloth.

544
00:26:54,621 --> 00:26:55,771
- This tastes like sap.

545
00:26:57,356 --> 00:26:59,386
- Jimmer, where's your Chevy?

546
00:26:59,386 --> 00:27:00,666
- Shook a shit.

547
00:27:00,666 --> 00:27:01,546
- I know that, eh?

548
00:27:01,546 --> 00:27:03,826
Where'd you leave it, out on 35?

549
00:27:03,826 --> 00:27:05,466
- I leaves it at the road.

550
00:27:05,466 --> 00:27:07,136
- Which road, the road into camp?

551
00:27:07,136 --> 00:27:09,106
- On the camp road!

552
00:27:09,106 --> 00:27:10,029
- Okay, all right.

553
00:27:11,146 --> 00:27:14,856
What do you say we climb
down, jump in the truck,

554
00:27:14,856 --> 00:27:16,885
see if we can get it started, eh?

555
00:27:16,885 --> 00:27:18,026
(Jimmer speaks gibberish)

556
00:27:18,026 --> 00:27:19,086
- Shames?

557
00:27:19,086 --> 00:27:21,229
- Shames, shames, shames!

558
00:27:23,956 --> 00:27:25,080
(Jimmer screams)

559
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:27,172
- Calm down, just calm down.

560
00:27:27,172 --> 00:27:28,005
Calm down.

561
00:27:28,005 --> 00:27:31,505
(Jimmer speaks gibberish)

562
00:27:32,918 --> 00:27:36,143
(car rattles)

563
00:27:36,143 --> 00:27:38,255
- My Chevy shook a shit.

564
00:27:38,255 --> 00:27:41,755
(Jimmer speaks gibberish)

565
00:27:47,209 --> 00:27:49,761
So, as I was walking (indistinct)

566
00:27:49,761 --> 00:27:51,121
down the (indistinct) road.

567
00:27:51,121 --> 00:27:52,245
(Jimmer speaks gibberish)

568
00:27:52,245 --> 00:27:53,635
Til all of a sudden.

569
00:27:53,635 --> 00:27:55,166
(fire crackles)

570
00:27:55,166 --> 00:27:58,813
(Jimmer speaks gibberish)

571
00:27:58,813 --> 00:27:59,705
(car revs)

572
00:27:59,705 --> 00:28:02,745
Then, the strangest thing happened.

573
00:28:02,745 --> 00:28:07,745
(Jimmer screams)
(horn honks)

574
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:10,833
(Jimmer whimpers)

575
00:28:14,248 --> 00:28:16,506
I think I shit myself.

576
00:28:16,506 --> 00:28:18,570
(bluesy music)

577
00:28:18,570 --> 00:28:21,086
- Remnar, get the Jimmer a towel.

578
00:28:21,086 --> 00:28:22,536
- You get the Jimmer a towel.

579
00:28:24,108 --> 00:28:25,498
- [Albert] Goddamn it!

580
00:28:25,498 --> 00:28:27,463
Jesus Christ!
- Pop!

581
00:28:27,463 --> 00:28:30,380
(Albert grumbling)

582
00:28:33,212 --> 00:28:34,045
Pop!

583
00:28:35,208 --> 00:28:38,125
(glass shattering)

584
00:28:43,626 --> 00:28:44,569
Pop, what's wrong?

585
00:28:46,586 --> 00:28:48,319
- It's all sap.

586
00:28:49,406 --> 00:28:51,579
Right out of the tree, sap.

587
00:28:54,826 --> 00:28:56,016
- The whole batch?

588
00:28:56,016 --> 00:28:58,769
- All that's missing is the
pancakes and the butter.

589
00:29:00,954 --> 00:29:05,797
- Mr. Soady, does that means?

590
00:29:05,797 --> 00:29:07,509
- I'm afraid so, Jimmer.

591
00:29:09,206 --> 00:29:11,219
We're in deer camp without whisky.

592
00:29:20,246 --> 00:29:23,529
- If I didn't know better,
I'd say this camp was.

593
00:29:31,016 --> 00:29:32,956
Holy Mary, Mother of God.

594
00:29:32,956 --> 00:29:35,176
- [Albert] If we'd had had
an ounce of sense amongst us,

595
00:29:35,176 --> 00:29:38,806
we'd have drove back to
Escanaba as fast as we could,

596
00:29:38,806 --> 00:29:41,976
but, as Great-Grandpa
Alphonse always used to say,

597
00:29:41,976 --> 00:29:43,873
if you're looking back
at the things you missed,

598
00:29:43,873 --> 00:29:45,569
you won't know what hit ya.

599
00:29:47,216 --> 00:29:48,696
- Let's have a pasty, eh?

600
00:29:48,696 --> 00:29:49,766
- Shasties!

601
00:29:49,766 --> 00:29:51,626
- Mom made the best pasties, remember?

602
00:29:51,626 --> 00:29:53,036
Remember how Ma used to make 'em?

603
00:29:53,036 --> 00:29:55,226
- Nobody built a pasty like your mother.

604
00:29:55,226 --> 00:29:57,776
- They were so good I could
almost eat six of them.

605
00:29:59,130 --> 00:30:00,819
- We ain't having pasties this year.

606
00:30:04,316 --> 00:30:05,236
- We ain't what?

607
00:30:06,300 --> 00:30:08,717
(gun clicks)

608
00:30:15,417 --> 00:30:19,306
- I don't know, thought we
might eat something different.

609
00:30:19,306 --> 00:30:20,196
- Not at deer camp.

610
00:30:20,196 --> 00:30:22,329
- At deer camp, we eat pasties.

611
00:30:23,256 --> 00:30:24,556
- Well, you know, I just
thought it might change

612
00:30:24,556 --> 00:30:26,156
our luck if we ate something else.

613
00:30:26,156 --> 00:30:27,306
- My luck's just fine the way it is,

614
00:30:27,306 --> 00:30:29,326
thank you very much.

615
00:30:29,326 --> 00:30:30,716
- Speak for yourself, eh?

616
00:30:30,716 --> 00:30:32,744
- I do believe I was, eh?

617
00:30:32,744 --> 00:30:33,911
- No shasties?

618
00:30:34,836 --> 00:30:37,656
- Let me remind you, eh, that pasties

619
00:30:37,656 --> 00:30:39,106
have been the traditional meal of choice

620
00:30:39,106 --> 00:30:41,526
since Great-Grandpa Alphonse
first built this camp.

621
00:30:41,526 --> 00:30:42,526
- Change is good.

622
00:30:42,526 --> 00:30:43,676
- Reuben, listen to me.

623
00:30:44,596 --> 00:30:46,796
We've known each other since we was kids.

624
00:30:46,796 --> 00:30:47,696
- We're brothers, Remnar.

625
00:30:47,696 --> 00:30:48,956
- Hear me out.

626
00:30:48,956 --> 00:30:52,704
You know how I can be a
little bit superstitious?

627
00:30:52,704 --> 00:30:55,537
(Jimmer chuckles)

628
00:30:57,666 --> 00:30:59,696
Any change in my deer camp ritual,

629
00:30:59,696 --> 00:31:01,816
big or small, directly deflects the odds

630
00:31:01,816 --> 00:31:03,476
of me bagging a big buck.

631
00:31:03,476 --> 00:31:05,676
Every year, I pack up
my truck the same way.

632
00:31:05,676 --> 00:31:07,106
I arrive at camp at the same time.

633
00:31:07,106 --> 00:31:09,056
I wake up opening
morning at the same time.

634
00:31:09,056 --> 00:31:11,346
4:44 am on the dot.

635
00:31:11,346 --> 00:31:13,386
I go to the same blind
by way of the same route

636
00:31:13,386 --> 00:31:15,006
with the same gun, the same buck calls,

637
00:31:15,006 --> 00:31:18,346
and the same Spam and mayonnaise
on Bunny bread sandwich.

638
00:31:18,346 --> 00:31:21,146
Everything is exactly the same.

639
00:31:21,146 --> 00:31:22,689
Even the shirt on my back.

640
00:31:24,656 --> 00:31:26,606
I've worn this same
shirt every opening day

641
00:31:26,606 --> 00:31:27,939
since the age of nine.

642
00:31:28,956 --> 00:31:29,966
Does it fit?

643
00:31:29,966 --> 00:31:31,056
No.

644
00:31:31,056 --> 00:31:32,986
Does it keep me warm?

645
00:31:32,986 --> 00:31:34,146
No.

646
00:31:34,146 --> 00:31:34,979
Does it smell?

647
00:31:34,979 --> 00:31:35,899
Most definitely.

648
00:31:36,956 --> 00:31:39,506
But does it guarantee the
big buck for yours truly?

649
00:31:40,756 --> 00:31:41,589
You betcha.

650
00:31:42,936 --> 00:31:44,516
Why?

651
00:31:44,516 --> 00:31:47,459
Because it's part of Remnar
Soady's deer camp ritual.

652
00:31:48,546 --> 00:31:51,746
A ritual that includes eating pasties.

653
00:31:51,746 --> 00:31:53,186
- You wanna know what
happens every time I eat

654
00:31:53,186 --> 00:31:54,616
pasties at deer camp?
- No.

655
00:31:54,616 --> 00:31:58,446
- No, three decades of meat,
potatoes, rutabagas, and lard.

656
00:31:58,446 --> 00:31:59,776
Every year, I go out to my blind,

657
00:31:59,776 --> 00:32:01,356
and I'm sitting out there
waiting for first light,

658
00:32:01,356 --> 00:32:02,886
and the only sound I hear is the sound

659
00:32:02,886 --> 00:32:05,586
of myself farting like a
tuba at the back of the band.

660
00:32:06,465 --> 00:32:08,516
- Pasties is a Soady tradition.

661
00:32:08,516 --> 00:32:09,889
- I know that very much.

662
00:32:11,336 --> 00:32:14,389
But I got a vision,
too, Remnar, a real one.

663
00:32:16,886 --> 00:32:18,919
I see myself coming back from camp,

664
00:32:20,116 --> 00:32:22,009
carrying a 10-pointer on my back,

665
00:32:24,402 --> 00:32:26,889
and my wife looks out, and I say to her,

666
00:32:29,473 --> 00:32:30,943
"Put on the lard and onions, honey,

667
00:32:30,943 --> 00:32:33,186
"I'm gonna gut you a buck."

668
00:32:33,186 --> 00:32:36,736
And I am happy at last,
knowing that I, Reuben Soady,

669
00:32:36,736 --> 00:32:39,219
have finally put the meat
on my family's table.

670
00:32:40,170 --> 00:32:42,753
(gentle music)

671
00:32:54,749 --> 00:32:58,529
- (sighs) I'll give it
a go for you, Reuben.

672
00:33:01,033 --> 00:33:01,866
Sure.

673
00:33:08,870 --> 00:33:09,703
Remnar?

674
00:33:14,596 --> 00:33:17,086
You're a deer in my headlights, Remnar.

675
00:33:20,447 --> 00:33:23,969
- (sighs) For this year only.

676
00:33:26,226 --> 00:33:29,577
- Thank you, Remnar, thank you very much!

677
00:33:29,577 --> 00:33:31,304
- [Jimmer] This is real nice.

678
00:33:31,304 --> 00:33:32,386
- [Reuben] You won't be sorry, I promise.

679
00:33:32,386 --> 00:33:34,621
- Ah, you just bag that buck this year.

680
00:33:34,621 --> 00:33:35,454
- Oh, I will, I can feel it.

681
00:33:35,454 --> 00:33:37,886
Maybe I'll even bag me a state record, eh?

682
00:33:37,886 --> 00:33:40,250
- You see anything foraging, fire away.

683
00:33:40,250 --> 00:33:42,790
- (laughs) I'd love to go tonight.

684
00:33:42,790 --> 00:33:45,540
(men chattering)

685
00:33:56,496 --> 00:33:58,853
- [Jimmer] I do some of
my best huntings at night.

686
00:33:58,853 --> 00:34:00,343
(Reuben laughs)

687
00:34:00,343 --> 00:34:03,843
(Jimmer speaks gibberish)

688
00:34:05,376 --> 00:34:07,986
- I can eat slapjacks
every day of the weeks, eh?

689
00:34:07,986 --> 00:34:09,286
- I know you could, Jimmer.

690
00:34:09,286 --> 00:34:10,926
- No, not flapjacks.

691
00:34:10,926 --> 00:34:12,166
- Y'all don't like the slapjacks?

692
00:34:12,166 --> 00:34:14,046
- Macaroni and cheese,
thank you very much.

693
00:34:14,046 --> 00:34:15,868
- With Spam.
- With Spam.

694
00:34:15,868 --> 00:34:17,416
- How's about slapjacks with Spams?

695
00:34:17,416 --> 00:34:18,373
- Fellas-

696
00:34:18,373 --> 00:34:19,726
- Just Spam for me.

697
00:34:19,726 --> 00:34:21,946
- Kraft macaroni and cheese.

698
00:34:21,946 --> 00:34:24,866
- No flapjacks, no macaroni
and cheese, and no Spam.

699
00:34:24,866 --> 00:34:25,906
- No Spam?

700
00:34:25,906 --> 00:34:27,796
- Boys, you are not only
going to eat like kings,

701
00:34:27,796 --> 00:34:29,026
but that 20 bucks you was gonna throw

702
00:34:29,026 --> 00:34:31,116
in the kitty for pasties, keep it.

703
00:34:31,116 --> 00:34:34,286
I am about to feed the whole camp all week

704
00:34:34,286 --> 00:34:36,009
for absolutely free.

705
00:34:37,418 --> 00:34:38,736
- [Albert Voiceover] As
Grandpa Alphonse always said,

706
00:34:38,736 --> 00:34:41,296
anything free is worth saving up for.

707
00:34:41,296 --> 00:34:42,876
- Last month, I was
sitting down to supper.

708
00:34:42,876 --> 00:34:44,256
Wolf Moon Dance comes out of the kitchen.

709
00:34:44,256 --> 00:34:45,916
She says, "Here, drink this."

710
00:34:45,916 --> 00:34:47,136
I didn't know what the heck it was.

711
00:34:47,136 --> 00:34:48,316
So I said, "What the heck is it, eh?

712
00:34:48,316 --> 00:34:50,743
She said, "There is more to bagging a buck

713
00:34:50,743 --> 00:34:52,366
"than just shooting a gun."

714
00:34:52,366 --> 00:34:54,623
- No shit, Cheyenne.

715
00:34:54,623 --> 00:34:55,456
- Yeah, she said that before every hunt,

716
00:34:55,456 --> 00:34:57,986
the Ojibwes prepare a special recipe

717
00:34:57,986 --> 00:34:59,806
to give the hunters good luck.

718
00:34:59,806 --> 00:35:02,116
Before they can even enter the woods,

719
00:35:02,116 --> 00:35:06,166
they believe that they have to
have the right air-a around.

720
00:35:06,166 --> 00:35:07,016
- The right what?

721
00:35:08,330 --> 00:35:09,586
- Air-a.

722
00:35:09,586 --> 00:35:10,496
- What's a air-a.

723
00:35:11,375 --> 00:35:13,006
- It's the air around you.

724
00:35:13,006 --> 00:35:14,436
- We all got a air-a?

725
00:35:15,286 --> 00:35:18,346
- Yeah, well, you know, at
least you're supposed to.

726
00:35:18,346 --> 00:35:20,186
- I can feels my airish.

727
00:35:20,186 --> 00:35:21,386
- That's good, Jimmer.

728
00:35:21,386 --> 00:35:24,309
- How do you know when the
air around ya is your air-a?

729
00:35:25,536 --> 00:35:27,466
- Your air is your air-a.

730
00:35:27,466 --> 00:35:29,266
- Is my air-a my air?

731
00:35:29,266 --> 00:35:30,446
- Just do the ritual, Remnar.

732
00:35:30,446 --> 00:35:31,546
- Reuben, I'm just trying

733
00:35:31,546 --> 00:35:32,874
to be clear here.
- Wait a minute,

734
00:35:32,874 --> 00:35:33,716
we ain't gonna strip down to our skivvies

735
00:35:33,716 --> 00:35:36,913
and dance around the table
like we did last Thanksgiving?

736
00:35:36,913 --> 00:35:37,792
- Involved, no-
- No offense to

737
00:35:37,792 --> 00:35:39,125
your Injun wife, but if
that's what I gotta do

738
00:35:39,125 --> 00:35:40,196
to get a piece of turkey
over to your place,

739
00:35:40,196 --> 00:35:41,256
I'll see you at Christmas.

740
00:35:41,256 --> 00:35:43,036
- You do not have to do any of that!

741
00:35:43,036 --> 00:35:44,486
I promise.

742
00:35:44,486 --> 00:35:46,204
- Thank you very much for that.

743
00:35:46,204 --> 00:35:48,288
- All you have to do is drink this potion.

744
00:35:48,288 --> 00:35:49,121
- This what?

745
00:35:49,121 --> 00:35:49,954
- Follow me.

746
00:35:53,806 --> 00:35:55,286
- Did he say potion.

747
00:35:55,286 --> 00:35:56,609
- I heard him say potion.

748
00:35:59,826 --> 00:36:01,039
They're kinda yellow, don't you think?

749
00:36:01,039 --> 00:36:02,414
- [Remnar] I don't know what those are.

750
00:36:02,414 --> 00:36:03,247
They look like cheese.

751
00:36:03,247 --> 00:36:04,649
- [Reuben] It's not cheese.

752
00:36:04,649 --> 00:36:06,481
- [Remnar] Okay, but I do enjoy cheese.

753
00:36:06,481 --> 00:36:09,381
- [Albert] Oh, so do I, but
it's cold on the bottom there.

754
00:36:10,578 --> 00:36:11,455
- [Reuben] Yeah, it's just like-

755
00:36:11,455 --> 00:36:12,288
- [Albert] Why do you got two of them for?

756
00:36:12,288 --> 00:36:13,159
- This one's Jimmer's.

757
00:36:14,593 --> 00:36:15,457
- Is it tasty?

758
00:36:15,457 --> 00:36:16,290
- Oh, it's definitely got a taste to it,

759
00:36:16,290 --> 00:36:17,469
no doubt about that.

760
00:36:17,469 --> 00:36:18,302
- Oh!

761
00:36:18,302 --> 00:36:19,135
- Is this what we're supposed to eat?

762
00:36:19,135 --> 00:36:20,226
- Oh yeah, yeah, that's very filling.

763
00:36:20,226 --> 00:36:21,526
One glass, three times a day,

764
00:36:21,526 --> 00:36:23,246
and not only will your air-a be so strong,

765
00:36:23,246 --> 00:36:24,079
instead of you hunting the bucks,

766
00:36:24,079 --> 00:36:25,383
